{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"A few months ago"},{"time":2000,"text":"the Nobel Prize in physics"},{"time":4000,"text":"was awarded to two teams of astronomers"},{"time":6000,"text":"for a discovery that has been hailed"},{"time":9000,"text":"as one of the most important"},{"time":11000,"text":"astronomical observations ever."},{"time":13000,"text":"And today, after briefly describing what they found,"},{"time":15000,"text":"I'm going to tell you about a highly controversial framework"},{"time":18000,"text":"for explaining their discovery,"},{"time":21000,"text":"namely the possibility"},{"time":23000,"text":"that way beyond the Earth,"},{"time":25000,"text":"the Milky Way and other distant galaxies,"},{"time":28000,"text":"we may find that our universe"},{"time":30000,"text":"is not the only universe,"},{"time":32000,"text":"but is instead"},{"time":34000,"text":"part of a vast complex of universes"},{"time":36000,"text":"that we call the multiverse."}]},{"cues":[{"time":38000,"text":"Now the idea of a multiverse is a strange one."},{"time":41000,"text":"I mean, most of us were raised to believe"},{"time":43000,"text":"that the word \"universe\" means everything."},{"time":46000,"text":"And I say most of us with forethought,"},{"time":49000,"text":"as my four-year-old daughter has heard me speak of these ideas since she was born."},{"time":52000,"text":"And last year I was holding her"},{"time":54000,"text":"and I said, \"Sophia,"},{"time":56000,"text":"I love you more than anything in the universe.\""},{"time":59000,"text":"And she turned to me and said, \"Daddy,"},{"time":61000,"text":"universe or multiverse?\""},{"time":63000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":66000,"text":"But barring such an anomalous upbringing,"},{"time":69000,"text":"it is strange to imagine"},{"time":71000,"text":"other realms separate from ours,"},{"time":73000,"text":"most with fundamentally different features,"},{"time":75000,"text":"that would rightly be called universes of their own."},{"time":78000,"text":"And yet,"},{"time":80000,"text":"speculative though the idea surely is,"},{"time":82000,"text":"I aim to convince you"},{"time":84000,"text":"that there's reason for taking it seriously,"},{"time":86000,"text":"as it just might be right."},{"time":88000,"text":"I'm going to tell the story of the multiverse in three parts."},{"time":91000,"text":"In part one,"},{"time":93000,"text":"I'm going to describe those Nobel Prize-winning results"},{"time":95000,"text":"and to highlight a profound mystery"},{"time":97000,"text":"which those results revealed."},{"time":99000,"text":"In part two,"},{"time":101000,"text":"I'll offer a solution to that mystery."},{"time":103000,"text":"It's based on an approach called string theory,"},{"time":105000,"text":"and that's where the idea of the multiverse"},{"time":107000,"text":"will come into the story."},{"time":109000,"text":"Finally, in part three,"},{"time":111000,"text":"I'm going to describe a cosmological theory"},{"time":113000,"text":"called inflation,"},{"time":115000,"text":"which will pull all the pieces of the story together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118000,"text":"Okay, part one starts back in 1929"},{"time":122000,"text":"when the great astronomer Edwin Hubble"},{"time":124000,"text":"realized that the distant galaxies"},{"time":127000,"text":"were all rushing away from us,"},{"time":129000,"text":"establishing that space itself is stretching,"},{"time":131000,"text":"it's expanding."},{"time":133000,"text":"Now this was revolutionary."},{"time":136000,"text":"The prevailing wisdom was that on the largest of scales"},{"time":139000,"text":"the universe was static."},{"time":141000,"text":"But even so,"},{"time":143000,"text":"there was one thing that everyone was certain of:"},{"time":146000,"text":"The expansion must be slowing down."},{"time":149000,"text":"That, much as the gravitational pull of the Earth"},{"time":152000,"text":"slows the ascent of an apple tossed upward,"},{"time":155000,"text":"the gravitational pull"},{"time":157000,"text":"of each galaxy on every other"},{"time":159000,"text":"must be slowing"},{"time":161000,"text":"the expansion of space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":163000,"text":"Now let's fast-forward to the 1990s"},{"time":166000,"text":"when those two teams of astronomers"},{"time":168000,"text":"I mentioned at the outset"},{"time":170000,"text":"were inspired by this reasoning"},{"time":172000,"text":"to measure the rate"},{"time":174000,"text":"at which the expansion has been slowing."},{"time":176000,"text":"And they did this"},{"time":178000,"text":"by painstaking observations"},{"time":180000,"text":"of numerous distant galaxies,"},{"time":182000,"text":"allowing them to chart"},{"time":184000,"text":"how the expansion rate has changed over time."},{"time":187000,"text":"Here's the surprise:"},{"time":190000,"text":"They found that the expansion is not slowing down."},{"time":193000,"text":"Instead they found that it's speeding up,"},{"time":195000,"text":"going faster and faster."},{"time":197000,"text":"That's like tossing an apple upward"},{"time":199000,"text":"and it goes up faster and faster."},{"time":201000,"text":"Now if you saw an apple do that,"},{"time":203000,"text":"you'd want to know why."},{"time":205000,"text":"What's pushing on it?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":207000,"text":"Similarly, the astronomers' results"},{"time":209000,"text":"are surely well-deserving of the Nobel Prize,"},{"time":212000,"text":"but they raised an analogous question."},{"time":216000,"text":"What force is driving all galaxies"},{"time":218000,"text":"to rush away from every other"},{"time":221000,"text":"at an ever-quickening speed?"},{"time":224000,"text":"Well the most promising answer"},{"time":226000,"text":"comes from an old idea of Einstein's."},{"time":229000,"text":"You see, we are all used to gravity"},{"time":231000,"text":"being a force that does one thing,"},{"time":234000,"text":"pulls objects together."},{"time":236000,"text":"But in Einstein's theory of gravity,"},{"time":238000,"text":"his general theory of relativity,"},{"time":240000,"text":"gravity can also push things apart."}]},{"cues":[{"time":243000,"text":"How? Well according to Einstein's math,"},{"time":246000,"text":"if space is uniformly filled"},{"time":248000,"text":"with an invisible energy,"},{"time":250000,"text":"sort of like a uniform, invisible mist,"},{"time":253000,"text":"then the gravity generated by that mist"},{"time":256000,"text":"would be repulsive,"},{"time":258000,"text":"repulsive gravity,"},{"time":260000,"text":"which is just what we need to explain the observations."},{"time":263000,"text":"Because the repulsive gravity"},{"time":265000,"text":"of an invisible energy in space --"},{"time":267000,"text":"we now call it dark energy,"},{"time":269000,"text":"but I've made it smokey white here so you can see it --"},{"time":272000,"text":"its repulsive gravity"},{"time":274000,"text":"would cause each galaxy to push against every other,"},{"time":276000,"text":"driving expansion to speed up,"},{"time":278000,"text":"not slow down."},{"time":280000,"text":"And this explanation"},{"time":282000,"text":"represents great progress."}]},{"cues":[{"time":284000,"text":"But I promised you a mystery"},{"time":287000,"text":"here in part one."},{"time":289000,"text":"Here it is."},{"time":291000,"text":"When the astronomers worked out"},{"time":293000,"text":"how much of this dark energy"},{"time":296000,"text":"must be infusing space"},{"time":298000,"text":"to account for the cosmic speed up,"},{"time":300000,"text":"look at what they found."},{"time":309000,"text":"This number is small."},{"time":311000,"text":"Expressed in the relevant unit,"},{"time":313000,"text":"it is spectacularly small."},{"time":315000,"text":"And the mystery is to explain this peculiar number."},{"time":318000,"text":"We want this number"},{"time":320000,"text":"to emerge from the laws of physics,"},{"time":322000,"text":"but so far no one has found a way to do that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":325000,"text":"Now you might wonder,"},{"time":328000,"text":"should you care?"},{"time":330000,"text":"Maybe explaining this number"},{"time":332000,"text":"is just a technical issue,"},{"time":334000,"text":"a technical detail of interest to experts,"},{"time":337000,"text":"but of no relevance to anybody else."},{"time":339000,"text":"Well it surely is a technical detail,"},{"time":342000,"text":"but some details really matter."},{"time":344000,"text":"Some details provide"},{"time":346000,"text":"windows into uncharted realms of reality,"},{"time":348000,"text":"and this peculiar number may be doing just that,"},{"time":351000,"text":"as the only approach that's so far made headway to explain it"},{"time":354000,"text":"invokes the possibility of other universes --"},{"time":357000,"text":"an idea that naturally emerges from string theory,"},{"time":360000,"text":"which takes me to part two: string theory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":363000,"text":"So hold the mystery of the dark energy"},{"time":367000,"text":"in the back of your mind"},{"time":369000,"text":"as I now go on to tell you"},{"time":371000,"text":"three key things about string theory."},{"time":374000,"text":"First off, what is it?"},{"time":376000,"text":"Well it's an approach to realize Einstein's dream"},{"time":379000,"text":"of a unified theory of physics,"},{"time":382000,"text":"a single overarching framework"},{"time":384000,"text":"that would be able to describe"},{"time":386000,"text":"all the forces at work in the universe."},{"time":388000,"text":"And the central idea of string theory"},{"time":390000,"text":"is quite straightforward."},{"time":392000,"text":"It says that if you examine"},{"time":394000,"text":"any piece of matter ever more finely,"},{"time":396000,"text":"at first you'll find molecules"},{"time":398000,"text":"and then you'll find atoms and subatomic particles."},{"time":401000,"text":"But the theory says that if you could probe smaller,"},{"time":403000,"text":"much smaller than we can with existing technology,"},{"time":406000,"text":"you'd find something else inside these particles --"},{"time":409000,"text":"a little tiny vibrating filament of energy,"},{"time":412000,"text":"a little tiny vibrating string."},{"time":415000,"text":"And just like the strings on a violin,"},{"time":417000,"text":"they can vibrate in different patterns"},{"time":419000,"text":"producing different musical notes."},{"time":421000,"text":"These little fundamental strings,"},{"time":423000,"text":"when they vibrate in different patterns,"},{"time":425000,"text":"they produce different kinds of particles --"},{"time":427000,"text":"so electrons, quarks, neutrinos, photons,"},{"time":429000,"text":"all other particles"},{"time":431000,"text":"would be united into a single framework,"},{"time":433000,"text":"as they would all arise from vibrating strings."},{"time":436000,"text":"It's a compelling picture,"},{"time":439000,"text":"a kind of cosmic symphony,"},{"time":441000,"text":"where all the richness"},{"time":443000,"text":"that we see in the world around us"},{"time":445000,"text":"emerges from the music"},{"time":447000,"text":"that these little, tiny strings can play."}]},{"cues":[{"time":450000,"text":"But there's a cost"},{"time":452000,"text":"to this elegant unification,"},{"time":454000,"text":"because years of research"},{"time":456000,"text":"have shown that the math of string theory doesn't quite work."},{"time":459000,"text":"It has internal inconsistencies,"},{"time":461000,"text":"unless we allow"},{"time":463000,"text":"for something wholly unfamiliar --"},{"time":466000,"text":"extra dimensions of space."},{"time":469000,"text":"That is, we all know about the usual three dimensions of space."},{"time":472000,"text":"And you can think about those"},{"time":474000,"text":"as height, width and depth."},{"time":477000,"text":"But string theory says that, on fantastically small scales,"},{"time":480000,"text":"there are additional dimensions"},{"time":482000,"text":"crumpled to a tiny size so small"},{"time":484000,"text":"that we have not detected them."},{"time":486000,"text":"But even though the dimensions are hidden,"},{"time":488000,"text":"they would have an impact on things that we can observe"},{"time":491000,"text":"because the shape of the extra dimensions"},{"time":494000,"text":"constrains how the strings can vibrate."},{"time":497000,"text":"And in string theory,"},{"time":499000,"text":"vibration determines everything."},{"time":502000,"text":"So particle masses, the strengths of forces,"},{"time":504000,"text":"and most importantly, the amount of dark energy"},{"time":507000,"text":"would be determined"},{"time":509000,"text":"by the shape of the extra dimensions."},{"time":511000,"text":"So if we knew the shape of the extra dimensions,"},{"time":514000,"text":"we should be able to calculate these features,"},{"time":517000,"text":"calculate the amount of dark energy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":520000,"text":"The challenge"},{"time":522000,"text":"is we don't know"},{"time":524000,"text":"the shape of the extra dimensions."},{"time":527000,"text":"All we have"},{"time":529000,"text":"is a list of candidate shapes"},{"time":531000,"text":"allowed by the math."},{"time":534000,"text":"Now when these ideas were first developed,"},{"time":536000,"text":"there were only about five different candidate shapes,"},{"time":538000,"text":"so you can imagine"},{"time":540000,"text":"analyzing them one-by-one"},{"time":542000,"text":"to determine if any yield"},{"time":544000,"text":"the physical features we observe."},{"time":546000,"text":"But over time the list grew"},{"time":548000,"text":"as researchers found other candidate shapes."},{"time":550000,"text":"From five, the number grew into the hundreds and then the thousands --"},{"time":553000,"text":"A large, but still manageable, collection to analyze,"},{"time":556000,"text":"since after all,"},{"time":558000,"text":"graduate students need something to do."},{"time":561000,"text":"But then the list continued to grow"},{"time":563000,"text":"into the millions and the billions, until today."},{"time":566000,"text":"The list of candidate shapes"},{"time":568000,"text":"has soared to about 10 to the 500."}]},{"cues":[{"time":573000,"text":"So, what to do?"},{"time":576000,"text":"Well some researchers lost heart,"},{"time":579000,"text":"concluding that was so many candidate shapes for the extra dimensions,"},{"time":582000,"text":"each giving rise to different physical features,"},{"time":585000,"text":"string theory would never make"},{"time":587000,"text":"definitive, testable predictions."},{"time":589000,"text":"But others turned this issue on its head,"},{"time":593000,"text":"taking us to the possibility of a multiverse."},{"time":595000,"text":"Here's the idea."},{"time":597000,"text":"Maybe each of these shapes is on an equal footing with every other."},{"time":600000,"text":"Each is as real as every other,"},{"time":602000,"text":"in the sense"},{"time":604000,"text":"that there are many universes,"},{"time":606000,"text":"each with a different shape, for the extra dimensions."},{"time":609000,"text":"And this radical proposal"},{"time":611000,"text":"has a profound impact on this mystery:"},{"time":614000,"text":"the amount of dark energy revealed by the Nobel Prize-winning results."}]},{"cues":[{"time":617000,"text":"Because you see,"},{"time":619000,"text":"if there are other universes,"},{"time":622000,"text":"and if those universes"},{"time":624000,"text":"each have, say, a different shape for the extra dimensions,"},{"time":628000,"text":"then the physical features of each universe will be different,"},{"time":630000,"text":"and in particular,"},{"time":632000,"text":"the amount of dark energy in each universe"},{"time":634000,"text":"will be different."},{"time":636000,"text":"Which means that the mystery"},{"time":638000,"text":"of explaining the amount of dark energy we've now measured"},{"time":640000,"text":"would take on a wholly different character."},{"time":643000,"text":"In this context,"},{"time":645000,"text":"the laws of physics can't explain one number for the dark energy"},{"time":648000,"text":"because there isn't just one number,"},{"time":651000,"text":"there are many numbers."},{"time":653000,"text":"Which means"},{"time":655000,"text":"we have been asking the wrong question."},{"time":658000,"text":"It's that the right question to ask is,"},{"time":660000,"text":"why do we humans find ourselves in a universe"},{"time":663000,"text":"with a particular amount of dark energy we've measured"},{"time":666000,"text":"instead of any of the other possibilities"},{"time":669000,"text":"that are out there?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":671000,"text":"And that's a question on which we can make headway."},{"time":674000,"text":"Because those universes"},{"time":676000,"text":"that have much more dark energy than ours,"},{"time":678000,"text":"whenever matter tries to clump into galaxies,"},{"time":681000,"text":"the repulsive push of the dark energy is so strong"},{"time":684000,"text":"that it blows the clump apart"},{"time":686000,"text":"and galaxies don't form."},{"time":688000,"text":"And in those universes that have much less dark energy,"},{"time":691000,"text":"well they collapse back on themselves so quickly"},{"time":693000,"text":"that, again, galaxies don't form."},{"time":696000,"text":"And without galaxies, there are no stars, no planets"},{"time":699000,"text":"and no chance"},{"time":701000,"text":"for our form of life"},{"time":703000,"text":"to exist in those other universes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":705000,"text":"So we find ourselves in a universe"},{"time":707000,"text":"with the particular amount of dark energy we've measured"},{"time":710000,"text":"simply because our universe has conditions"},{"time":713000,"text":"hospitable to our form of life."},{"time":717000,"text":"And that would be that."},{"time":719000,"text":"Mystery solved,"},{"time":721000,"text":"multiverse found."},{"time":723000,"text":"Now some find this explanation unsatisfying."},{"time":728000,"text":"We're used to physics"},{"time":730000,"text":"giving us definitive explanations for the features we observe."},{"time":733000,"text":"But the point is,"},{"time":735000,"text":"if the feature you're observing"},{"time":738000,"text":"can and does take on"},{"time":740000,"text":"a wide variety of different values"},{"time":742000,"text":"across the wider landscape of reality,"},{"time":745000,"text":"then thinking one explanation"},{"time":747000,"text":"for a particular value"},{"time":749000,"text":"is simply misguided."}]},{"cues":[{"time":752000,"text":"An early example"},{"time":754000,"text":"comes from the great astronomer Johannes Kepler"},{"time":757000,"text":"who was obsessed with understanding"},{"time":759000,"text":"a different number --"},{"time":761000,"text":"why the Sun is 93 million miles away from the Earth."},{"time":765000,"text":"And he worked for decades trying to explain this number,"},{"time":768000,"text":"but he never succeeded, and we know why."},{"time":771000,"text":"Kepler was asking"},{"time":773000,"text":"the wrong question."}]},{"cues":[{"time":775000,"text":"We now know that there are many planets"},{"time":778000,"text":"at a wide variety of different distances from their host stars."},{"time":781000,"text":"So hoping that the laws of physics"},{"time":784000,"text":"will explain one particular number, 93 million miles,"},{"time":787000,"text":"well that is simply wrongheaded."},{"time":790000,"text":"Instead the right question to ask is,"},{"time":792000,"text":"why do we humans find ourselves on a planet"},{"time":795000,"text":"at this particular distance,"},{"time":797000,"text":"instead of any of the other possibilities?"},{"time":800000,"text":"And again, that's a question we can answer."},{"time":803000,"text":"Those planets which are much closer to a star like the Sun"},{"time":806000,"text":"would be so hot"},{"time":808000,"text":"that our form of life wouldn't exist."},{"time":810000,"text":"And those planets that are much farther away from the star,"},{"time":813000,"text":"well they're so cold"},{"time":815000,"text":"that, again, our form of life would not take hold."},{"time":817000,"text":"So we find ourselves"},{"time":819000,"text":"on a planet at this particular distance"},{"time":821000,"text":"simply because it yields conditions"},{"time":823000,"text":"vital to our form of life."},{"time":826000,"text":"And when it comes to planets and their distances,"},{"time":829000,"text":"this clearly is the right kind of reasoning."},{"time":833000,"text":"The point is,"},{"time":835000,"text":"when it comes to universes and the dark energy that they contain,"},{"time":838000,"text":"it may also be the right kind of reasoning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":842000,"text":"One key difference, of course,"},{"time":845000,"text":"is we know that there are other planets out there,"},{"time":847000,"text":"but so far I've only speculated on the possibility"},{"time":850000,"text":"that there might be other universes."},{"time":852000,"text":"So to pull it all together,"},{"time":854000,"text":"we need a mechanism"},{"time":856000,"text":"that can actually generate other universes."},{"time":859000,"text":"And that takes me to my final part, part three."},{"time":862000,"text":"Because such a mechanism has been found"},{"time":865000,"text":"by cosmologists trying to understand the Big Bang."},{"time":868000,"text":"You see, when we speak of the Big Bang,"},{"time":870000,"text":"we often have an image"},{"time":872000,"text":"of a kind of cosmic explosion"},{"time":874000,"text":"that created our universe"},{"time":876000,"text":"and set space rushing outward."}]},{"cues":[{"time":879000,"text":"But there's a little secret."},{"time":881000,"text":"The Big Bang leaves out something pretty important,"},{"time":884000,"text":"the Bang."},{"time":886000,"text":"It tells us how the universe evolved after the Bang,"},{"time":889000,"text":"but gives us no insight"},{"time":891000,"text":"into what would have powered the Bang itself."},{"time":895000,"text":"And this gap was finally filled"},{"time":897000,"text":"by an enhanced version of the Big Bang theory."},{"time":899000,"text":"It's called inflationary cosmology,"},{"time":902000,"text":"which identified a particular kind of fuel"},{"time":906000,"text":"that would naturally generate"},{"time":908000,"text":"an outward rush of space."},{"time":910000,"text":"The fuel is based on something called a quantum field,"},{"time":913000,"text":"but the only detail that matters for us"},{"time":916000,"text":"is that this fuel proves to be so efficient"},{"time":919000,"text":"that it's virtually impossible"},{"time":921000,"text":"to use it all up,"},{"time":923000,"text":"which means in the inflationary theory,"},{"time":925000,"text":"the Big Bang giving rise to our universe"},{"time":928000,"text":"is likely not a one-time event."},{"time":931000,"text":"Instead the fuel not only generated our Big Bang,"},{"time":934000,"text":"but it would also generate countless other Big Bangs,"},{"time":940000,"text":"each giving rise to its own separate universe"},{"time":943000,"text":"with our universe becoming but one bubble"},{"time":945000,"text":"in a grand cosmic bubble bath of universes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":948000,"text":"And now, when we meld this with string theory,"},{"time":950000,"text":"here's the picture we're led to."},{"time":952000,"text":"Each of these universes has extra dimensions."},{"time":954000,"text":"The extra dimensions take on a wide variety of different shapes."},{"time":957000,"text":"The different shapes yield different physical features."},{"time":960000,"text":"And we find ourselves in one universe instead of another"},{"time":963000,"text":"simply because it's only in our universe"},{"time":966000,"text":"that the physical features, like the amount of dark energy,"},{"time":969000,"text":"are right for our form of life to take hold."},{"time":973000,"text":"And this is the compelling but highly controversial picture"},{"time":976000,"text":"of the wider cosmos"},{"time":978000,"text":"that cutting-edge observation and theory"},{"time":980000,"text":"have now led us to seriously consider."}]},{"cues":[{"time":984000,"text":"One big remaining question, of course, is,"},{"time":988000,"text":"could we ever confirm"},{"time":991000,"text":"the existence of other universes?"},{"time":994000,"text":"Well let me describe"},{"time":996000,"text":"one way that might one day happen."},{"time":999000,"text":"The inflationary theory"},{"time":1001000,"text":"already has strong observational support."},{"time":1003000,"text":"Because the theory predicts"},{"time":1005000,"text":"that the Big Bang would have been so intense"},{"time":1007000,"text":"that as space rapidly expanded,"},{"time":1010000,"text":"tiny quantum jitters from the micro world"},{"time":1012000,"text":"would have been stretched out to the macro world,"},{"time":1015000,"text":"yielding a distinctive fingerprint,"},{"time":1018000,"text":"a pattern of slightly hotter spots and slightly colder spots,"},{"time":1020000,"text":"across space,"},{"time":1022000,"text":"which powerful telescopes have now observed."},{"time":1025000,"text":"Going further, if there are other universes,"},{"time":1028000,"text":"the theory predicts that every so often"},{"time":1030000,"text":"those universes can collide."},{"time":1032000,"text":"And if our universe got hit by another,"},{"time":1034000,"text":"that collision"},{"time":1036000,"text":"would generate an additional subtle pattern"},{"time":1038000,"text":"of temperature variations across space"},{"time":1040000,"text":"that we might one day"},{"time":1042000,"text":"be able to detect."},{"time":1044000,"text":"And so exotic as this picture is,"},{"time":1047000,"text":"it may one day be grounded"},{"time":1049000,"text":"in observations,"},{"time":1051000,"text":"establishing the existence of other universes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1054000,"text":"I'll conclude"},{"time":1056000,"text":"with a striking implication"},{"time":1059000,"text":"of all these ideas"},{"time":1061000,"text":"for the very far future."},{"time":1063000,"text":"You see, we learned"},{"time":1065000,"text":"that our universe is not static,"},{"time":1067000,"text":"that space is expanding,"},{"time":1069000,"text":"that that expansion is speeding up"},{"time":1071000,"text":"and that there might be other universes"},{"time":1073000,"text":"all by carefully examining"},{"time":1075000,"text":"faint pinpoints of starlight"},{"time":1077000,"text":"coming to us from distant galaxies."},{"time":1080000,"text":"But because the expansion is speeding up,"},{"time":1083000,"text":"in the very far future,"},{"time":1085000,"text":"those galaxies will rush away so far and so fast"},{"time":1088000,"text":"that we won't be able to see them --"},{"time":1091000,"text":"not because of technological limitations,"},{"time":1093000,"text":"but because of the laws of physics."},{"time":1095000,"text":"The light those galaxies emit,"},{"time":1097000,"text":"even traveling at the fastest speed, the speed of light,"},{"time":1100000,"text":"will not be able to overcome"},{"time":1102000,"text":"the ever-widening gulf between us."},{"time":1105000,"text":"So astronomers in the far future"},{"time":1107000,"text":"looking out into deep space"},{"time":1109000,"text":"will see nothing but an endless stretch"},{"time":1112000,"text":"of static, inky, black stillness."},{"time":1116000,"text":"And they will conclude"},{"time":1118000,"text":"that the universe is static and unchanging"},{"time":1120000,"text":"and populated by a single central oasis of matter"},{"time":1123000,"text":"that they inhabit --"},{"time":1125000,"text":"a picture of the cosmos"},{"time":1127000,"text":"that we definitively know to be wrong."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1130000,"text":"Now maybe those future astronomers will have records"},{"time":1133000,"text":"handed down from an earlier era,"},{"time":1135000,"text":"like ours,"},{"time":1137000,"text":"attesting to an expanding cosmos"},{"time":1139000,"text":"teeming with galaxies."},{"time":1141000,"text":"But would those future astronomers"},{"time":1143000,"text":"believe such ancient knowledge?"},{"time":1146000,"text":"Or would they believe"},{"time":1148000,"text":"in the black, static empty universe"},{"time":1151000,"text":"that their own state-of-the-art observations reveal?"},{"time":1155000,"text":"I suspect the latter."},{"time":1157000,"text":"Which means that we are living"},{"time":1159000,"text":"through a remarkably privileged era"},{"time":1162000,"text":"when certain deep truths about the cosmos"},{"time":1164000,"text":"are still within reach"},{"time":1166000,"text":"of the human spirit of exploration."},{"time":1168000,"text":"It appears that it may not always be that way."},{"time":1173000,"text":"Because today's astronomers,"},{"time":1175000,"text":"by turning powerful telescopes to the sky,"},{"time":1178000,"text":"have captured a handful of starkly informative photons --"},{"time":1181000,"text":"a kind of cosmic telegram"},{"time":1184000,"text":"billions of years in transit."},{"time":1186000,"text":"and the message echoing across the ages is clear."},{"time":1190000,"text":"Sometimes nature guards her secrets"},{"time":1193000,"text":"with the unbreakable grip"},{"time":1195000,"text":"of physical law."},{"time":1197000,"text":"Sometimes the true nature of reality beckons"},{"time":1201000,"text":"from just beyond the horizon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1204000,"text":"Thank you very much."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1206000,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1210000,"text":"Chris Anderson: Brian, thank you."},{"time":1212000,"text":"The range of ideas you've just spoken about"},{"time":1214000,"text":"are dizzying, exhilarating, incredible."},{"time":1217000,"text":"How do you think"},{"time":1219000,"text":"of where cosmology is now,"},{"time":1221000,"text":"in a sort of historical side?"},{"time":1223000,"text":"Are we in the middle of something unusual historically in your opinion?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1226000,"text":"BG: Well it's hard to say."},{"time":1228000,"text":"When we learn that astronomers of the far future"},{"time":1231000,"text":"may not have enough information to figure things out,"},{"time":1234000,"text":"the natural question is, maybe we're already in that position"},{"time":1237000,"text":"and certain deep, critical features of the universe"},{"time":1240000,"text":"already have escaped our ability to understand"},{"time":1243000,"text":"because of how cosmology evolves."},{"time":1245000,"text":"So from that perspective,"},{"time":1247000,"text":"maybe we will always be asking questions"},{"time":1249000,"text":"and never be able to fully answer them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1251000,"text":"On the other hand, we now can understand"},{"time":1253000,"text":"how old the universe is."},{"time":1255000,"text":"We can understand"},{"time":1257000,"text":"how to understand the data from the microwave background radiation"},{"time":1260000,"text":"that was set down 13.72 billion years ago --"},{"time":1263000,"text":"and yet, we can do calculations today to predict how it will look"},{"time":1265000,"text":"and it matches."},{"time":1267000,"text":"Holy cow! That's just amazing."},{"time":1269000,"text":"So on the one hand, it's just incredible where we've gotten,"},{"time":1272000,"text":"but who knows what sort of blocks we may find in the future."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1276000,"text":"CA: You're going to be around for the next few days."},{"time":1279000,"text":"Maybe some of these conversations can continue."},{"time":1281000,"text":"Thank you. Thank you, Brian. (BG: My pleasure.)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1283000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}